<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7517] Preemptive fast fail exception should not be processed multiple times in the stack</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7517</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Preemptive fast fail exception is a mechanism to prevent client threads from blocking on talking to a unresponsive server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6629&quot; title=&quot;[0.89-fb] Fast fail client operations if the regionserver is repeatedly unreachable.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6629&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6629&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if a PFFE is thrown from an inner function (say locateRegionInMeta), then the outer functions should not process this exception as a failure in talking to the RS. We should just percolate this exception back to the client.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
